    "hypothesis_statement": "In USD-M perpetual futures, relatively high positive funding rates indicate crowded long exposure and should predict weaker subsequent price returns, while relatively low or negative funding rates indicate crowded short exposure or long compensation and should predict stronger subsequent price returns, after a no-lookahead availability lag.",
